      "acceptanceCriteria": "The validation QoI (hemolysis index) must directly correspond to the clinical decision QoI without surrogate substitution.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) used in validation corresponds to the clinical QoI; however, the power-law hemolysis model introduces a surrogate scalar that does not directly map to in-vivo red cell damage, limiting achievedLevel to 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/relevance-validation-cou2",
